								<div class="post-314169 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized tag-debt tag-federal-reserve tag-loans odd" id="post-314169">
						<div class="post-headline"><h2>				<a href="http://www.brotherjohnf.com/archives/314169" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Subprime loans repackaged &amp; sold as AAA debt caused the collapse of markets in 2007/2008. It’s happening again.">
				Subprime loans repackaged &#038; sold as AAA debt caused the collapse of markets in 2007/2008. It’s happening again.</a></h2></div>				<div class="post-bodycopy clearfix"><p>investmentwatchblog.com/ July 10, 2014</p>
